    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1IndirectValue" kindref="compound">Dali::IndirectValue</ref> is an intermediate object that enables a simpler syntax for addressing properties. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>@SINCE_1_9.27 object[&quot;property&quot;] = value; float value = object[&quot;property&quot;];</para>
<para>It is not intended to be directly instantiated, instead, any <ref refid="classDali_1_1Handle" kindref="compound">Handle</ref> type will generate a temporary object using the above syntax. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
